    </node>
    <node id="INTEGER">
      <data key="d0">DATA_TYPE</data>
      <data key="d1">The entity "INTEGER" is a data type that represents whole numbers, utilized for storing and analyzing numerical data, including attributes such as invoice numbers and customer IDs. This data type is specifically designed to handle whole numbers, making it an essential component in various data modeling and database design applications, particularly in the context of SQL instruction and data warehousing development. The INTEGER data type is widely used to store unique identifiers, quantitative values, and other types of numerical information, enabling efficient data analysis and processing. By leveraging the INTEGER data type, data architects and analysts can effectively manage and manipulate numerical data, gaining valuable insights and supporting informed decision-making processes.</data>
      <data key="d2">ae531614ad2754d6b083288c0595dfa5,d4c32cb337d90fe6c32a1507c69b61b3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="VARCHAR">
      <data key="d0">DATA_TYPE</data>
      <data key="d1">The VARCHAR entity is a data type that represents character strings, utilized for storing and analyzing text data, including attributes such as plans, service periods, and payment methods. It is primarily used for attributes that require text-based information, enabling the storage and analysis of character strings in a database. The VARCHAR data type is essential in database design, particularly in SQL instruction, as it allows for the efficient storage and retrieval of text data, making it a fundamental component in data modeling and data warehousing development.</data>
      <data key="d2">ae531614ad2754d6b083288c0595dfa5,d4c32cb337d90fe6c32a1507c69b61b3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INVOICE">
      <data key="d0">CONCEPT</data>
      <data key="d1">An invoice is a document that lists the goods or services provided to a customer, along with the amount due}</data>
      <data key="d2">ae531614ad2754d6b083288c0595dfa5</data>
    </node>
