    <edge source="STREAMS" target="CUSTOMER">
      <data key="d4">16.0</data>
      <data key="d5">A stream is associated with a customer, who streamed the content, and has a unique customer ID</data>
      <data key="d6">dcf10bbfcd07ccf54a18b52e04a4d891</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="STREAMS" target="CONTENT">
      <data key="d4">32.0</data>
      <data key="d5">The entities STREAMS and CONTENT are intricately related, with each content item being associated with one or more streams of data or information. These streams may pertain to viewer activity or engagement, highlighting the dynamic interaction between the content and its audience. Conversely, a stream is linked to specific content, which has been streamed, and is identifiable by a unique content ID. This reciprocal relationship underscores the interconnected nature of STREAMS and CONTENT, where content is disseminated through streams, and streams are defined by the content they carry. The unique content ID serves as a key identifier, facilitating the organization and analysis of the content within the context of the streams. Through this association, STREAMS and CONTENT collectively enable the tracking and understanding of content performance and viewer engagement, providing valuable insights into the efficacy of the streaming process.</data>
      <data key="d6">d4c32cb337d90fe6c32a1507c69b61b3,dcf10bbfcd07ccf54a18b52e04a4d891</data>
    </edge>
